4 SYNOPSIS:
5 This bill would create the Permanent Joint
6 Legislative Advisory Commission on Alabama Boys and Men
7 to study issues affecting boys and men and to advise
8 the Legislature on legislative and policy
9 recommendations.
10 This bill would provide for the membership and
11 duties of the commission.
12 This bill would require the commission to submit
13 a report of its findings and recommendations to the
14 Legislature each year.
15 This bill would also provide that the commission
16 would sunset on October 1, 2030.
17
18
19 A BILL
20 TO BE ENTITLED
21 AN ACT
22
23 Relating to the Legislature; to create the Permanent
24 Joint Legislative Advisory Commission on Alabama Boys and Men;
25 to provide for the membership and duties of the commission;
26 and to provide a sunset date for the commission.
27 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
28 Section 1. (a) There is created the Permanent Joint
